<p>Republicans do not govern to the majority.  The govern to their base.</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77002808,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3750262&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;19058290&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;aregularperson1&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">12 votes</div></li></ul></div><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c77002808" title="Link to this comment">#1.1</a> - Thu Jun 20, 2013 11:45 AM EDT</span></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody child " id="c77003877"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77003877,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;liberalbullyray&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;Liberal Bully Ray&quot;}"></div><a name="star3"></a><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="#star4" class="noborder star"><img src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_star.gif" width="16" height="16" alt="" title="Jump To Next Highly Rated Comment" /></a><a href="http://liberalbullyray.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://m.static.newsvine.com/servista/imagesizer?file=LiberalBullyRayA61C0CFA-2F6D-3E67-E4B0-8C9EEBB3CE74.jpg&width=60" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="false" /></a><a href="http://liberalbullyray.newsvine.com/">Liberal Bully Ray</a></div></div><div id="commentText_77003877" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>Very true!</p>
<p>90 percent of the population may want background checks on gun purchases, and 87 percent may want a path to citizenship for the illegals already here. But since 90 percent of the population can't vote in a Senatorial election, then why should they care, especially in the Red states?</p>
<p>So in a Red state, especially a southern red state, as long as the hicks, racists, paste eaters, knuckle draggers, and people out of touch with reality continue to vote for Republicans in their gerrymandered districts, the rest of the population can kick rocks as far as they are concerned.</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77003877,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3750262&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;19058290&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;liberalbullyray&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">6 votes</div></li></ul></div><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c77003877" title="Link to this comment">#1.2</a> - Thu Jun 20, 2013 12:26 PM EDT</span></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody child " id="c77004259"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77004259,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;fb-sheamageehan100003013302082&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;Shea Mageehan&quot;}"></div><a name="star4"></a><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="#star5" class="noborder star"><img src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_star.gif" width="16" height="16" alt="" title="Jump To Next Highly Rated Comment" /></a><a href="http://fb-sheamageehan100003013302082.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://m.static.newsvine.com/servista/imagesizer?file=local95EA6C90-8988-EF98-9050-3A8F7DE5C246.jpg&width=60" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="false" /></a><a href="http://fb-sheamageehan100003013302082.newsvine.com/">Shea Mageehan</a></div></div><div id="commentText_77004259" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>Face it..when elected officials simply ignore the wishes of the majority of the voters, then your government is broken. How on earth did America wind up in such a sorry state? And now you want to take the show on the road again, to Syria. For God's sake!</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77004259,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3750262&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;19058290&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;fb-sheamageehan100003013302082&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">5 votes</div></li></ul></div><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c77004259" title="Link to this comment">#1.3</a> - Thu Jun 20, 2013 12:42 PM EDT</span></div></div></div><div class="clearfix"><img class="replybutton" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_reply_mini.gif" width="35" height="12" alt="Reply" /></div><div class="commentcontainer"><span></span></div></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody " id="c77001853"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77001853,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;ronbyers&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;Ron Byers&quot;}"></div><a name="star5"></a><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="#star6" class="noborder star"><img src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_star.gif" width="16" height="16" alt="" title="Jump To Next Highly Rated Comment" /></a><a href="http://ronbyers.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/av/60x60/msnbc.jpg" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="true" /></a><a href="http://ronbyers.newsvine.com/">Ron Byers</a></div></div><div id="commentText_77001853" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p><em>GOP lawmakers are confident that attitudes in their red states and districts don't reflect national trends, so they couldn't care less what Americans in generally believe, so long as the folks who turn out for them on Election Day think the way they do.</em></p>
<p>Which is exactly why we need to fire all the Democratic consultants who share this belief.  The Democratic party needs to go into each Republican district and challenge the incumbent.  We might not win all of them, but we only need to win 25-30 to change America.   At the very least the Republicans will have to run to the middle to stay in office.</p>
<p>The first thing we do is fire the Democratic consultants whose minds frozen with the belief that the above quote is written in stone.  Democrats have no choice.  We have to challenge conventional wisdom.  Otherwise, we suffer another two years of this crap. </p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77001853,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3750262&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;19058290&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;ronbyers&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">7 votes</div></li></ul></div><img class="replybutton" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_reply_mini.gif" width="35" height="12" alt="Reply" /><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c77001853" title="Link to this comment">#2</a> - Thu Jun 20, 2013 11:06 AM EDT</span><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody child " id="c77002737"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77002737,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;cundgulag&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;c u n d gulag&quot;}"></div><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="http://cundgulag.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/av/60x60/msnbc.jpg" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="true" /></a><a href="http://cundgulag.newsvine.com/">c u n d gulag</a></div></div><div id="commentText_77002737" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>Ron,</p>
<p>I've long suspected that most of the Democratic "strategists," were/are 'Republicachurian Candidate Consultants.'</p>
<p>That they were Republican wolves, in Democratic union-made  wool suits - nowadays, that's a stretch (and I don't mean, 'stretch-wool, I mean, union-made).</p>
<p>Howard Dean was right - we have to do a 50 state, and every Congressional district, approach.</p>
<p>Don't cherry-pick - CHERRY BOMB!</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77002737,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3750262&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;19058290&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;cundgulag&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">3 votes</div></li></ul></div><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c77002737" title="Link to this comment">#2.1</a> - Thu Jun 20, 2013 11:42 AM EDT</span></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody child " id="c77003032"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77003032,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;jmul3144&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;jmul3144&quot;}"></div><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="http://jmul3144.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/av/60x60/msnbc.jpg" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="true" /></a><a href="http://jmul3144.newsvine.com/">jmul3144</a></div></div><div id="commentText_77003032" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>These folks who are spewing all kinds of crazy speak are stuck in a conundrum. They absolutely know that they are creating a fire storm but they also represent people that they and their predecessors brainwashed.Its not difficult to brainwash these simpletons.What now needs to be done is to take all these "Extreme Conservatives" to RE-HAB. They need to be cleansed of all the poison that has been injected into them by the clown car occupants.Then and only then can these characters do the right thing.The example of the woman who took the microphone from John McCain and called Obama an Arab.Thankfully McCain showed back bone and set her straight.</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77003032,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3750262&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;19058290&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;jmul3144&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">2 votes</div></li></ul></div><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c77003032" title="Link to this comment">#2.2</a> - Thu Jun 20, 2013 11:54 AM EDT</span></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody child " id="c77007285"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77007285,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;gardenladytoo&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;GardenLadyToo&quot;}"></div><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="http://gardenladytoo.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/av/60x60/msnbc.jpg" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="true" /></a><a href="http://gardenladytoo.newsvine.com/">GardenLadyToo</a></div></div><div id="commentText_77007285" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>I disagree.  It's not that we need to get rid of the "Democratic consultants".  It's that we need to find or create one or more groups who will hire independent, non-Democratic consultants, unbeholden to either party, who will advocate for the now-largest portion of the electorate--independents not affiliated with either party.</p>
</p>
<p>We need these group(s) to form their own think tanks to do the much-maligned "reality-based" research, to mobilize independents to get out and register to vote in the primaries of whichever party they hate the most, and then VOTE, in the primaries, for sane candidates.</p>
<p>So long as <em>both</em> parties are selecting their general election candidates through primaries that are only voted in by either-party zealots, we are going to be faced with neverending choices in general elections between Idiot A and Idiot B.</p>
<p>Those of us who favor reasonable, responsive, well-balanced government need to launch and fund a get-out-the-sane-vote campaign that's aimed at the primaries.</p>
<p>We need to grab both parties by the scruff of the neck, and make them choose between moderation and oblivion.</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77007285,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3750262&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;19058290&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;gardenladytoo&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">1 vote</div></li></ul></div><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c77007285" title="Link to this comment">#2.3</a> - Thu Jun 20, 2013 2:47 PM EDT</span></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody child " id="c77010600"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77010600,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;rwsgate&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;rwsgate&quot;}"></div><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="http://rwsgate.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://m.static.newsvine.com/servista/imagesizer?file=rwsgate9AB52126-D0D7-F60C-01C2-FE66DB5C91C5.jpg&width=60" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="false" /></a><a href="http://rwsgate.newsvine.com/">rwsgate</a></div></div><div id="commentText_77010600" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>Garden Lady-  I think you are overlooking the fact that there really aren't than many independent voters.  I would call them "unaffiliated" instead.  They choose not to register with either party.  Here in Arizona, these unaffiliated voters are about 1/3 of the electorate, but they identify and vote along party lines.</p>
<p>I don't agree that "both sides do it".  Look at the number of extremists on the right and then tell me we have as many, or as crazy, extremists on the left.</p>
<p>I agree with c u n d gulag that we have to go after every seat, including state offices.  There are far too many positions where there is no opposing candidate.  When we allow so many seats to be unchallenged, we allow for a concentration of money in the few seats that are in swing districts.  By forcing every candidate to defend his own turf, you also force candidates to moderate their approaches, as they will have to appeal to more people to retain their position.</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77010600,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3750262&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;19058290&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;rwsgate&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"></ul></div><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c77010600" title="Link to this comment">#2.4</a> - Thu Jun 20, 2013 4:38 PM EDT</span></div></div></div><div class="clearfix"><img class="replybutton" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_reply_mini.gif" width="35" height="12" alt="Reply" /></div><div class="commentcontainer"><span></span></div></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody " id="c77001897"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77001897,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;wallyobrien&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;Dogjudge&quot;}"></div><a name="star6"></a><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="#star7" class="noborder star"><img src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_star.gif" width="16" height="16" alt="" title="Jump To Next Highly Rated Comment" /></a><a href="http://wallyobrien.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/av/60x60/msnbc.jpg" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="true" /></a><a href="http://wallyobrien.newsvine.com/">Dogjudge</a></div></div><div id="commentText_77001897" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>87% of Americans are for this. Doesn't it naturally follow that the congressional Republicans would be against it?</p>
<p>At the same time, you get the same people who are for this re-electing the GOP cretins.</p>
<p>I'm especially surprised at their opposition considering that most businesses are for this.</p>
<p>Of course if we were talking about immigration of old, white, men into the country, the GOP might go for it.</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77001897,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3750262&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;19058290&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;wallyobrien&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">6 votes</div></li></ul></div><img class="replybutton" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_reply_mini.gif" width="35" height="12" alt="Reply" /><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c77001897" title="Link to this comment">#3</a> - Thu Jun 20, 2013 11:08 AM EDT</span><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody child " id="c77002259"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77002259,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;indialecarre&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;India LeCarre&quot;}"></div><a name="star7"></a><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="#star8" class="noborder star"><img src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_star.gif" width="16" height="16" alt="" title="Jump To Next Highly Rated Comment" /></a><a href="http://indialecarre.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://m.static.newsvine.com/servista/imagesizer?file=indialecarre2F26BA61-70D9-8959-DEA9-9191F1C85113.jpg&width=60" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="false" /></a><a href="http://indialecarre.newsvine.com/">India LeCarre</a></div></div><div id="commentText_77002259" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>I am just totally dismayed at the heartlessness of these Republicans.  Allowing these people to become citizens is the only practical and humane thing to do.</p>
<p>They will use border security as their excuse.  If we have<strong> a moat of hot, bubbling lava as a border</strong>, they will not see it as secure.  It is just a ruse for being cruel to immigrants who are living a shadow existence, and who should be able to live, work, and pay taxes like the rest of us.  These are not criminals, but average people who simply want to work and live in peace.</p>
<p>Shame on<strong> Ted Cruz</strong> most of all.  Send him back to Cuba.  See how <strong><em>he</em></strong> likes being put out to a  strange country after living here 40 years.</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77002259,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3750262&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;19058290&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;indialecarre&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">9 votes</div></li></ul></div><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c77002259" title="Link to this comment">#3.1</a> - Thu Jun 20, 2013 11:22 AM EDT</span></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody child " id="c77011120"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77011120,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;rwsgate&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;rwsgate&quot;}"></div><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="http://rwsgate.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://m.static.newsvine.com/servista/imagesizer?file=rwsgate9AB52126-D0D7-F60C-01C2-FE66DB5C91C5.jpg&width=60" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="false" /></a><a href="http://rwsgate.newsvine.com/">rwsgate</a></div></div><div id="commentText_77011120" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>India-  A moat of hot bubbling lava would never work, anyway.  How far would that have to extend into the Pacific or the Gulf of Mexico before it cooled off?  The hardest part for any illegal is just getting across the border.  It's relatively easy to disappear once you're here.  Come by boat, by plane, by car.  Get a passport, say you're visiting, or shopping, or something.  Come in through Canada.  Unless you've got a criminal record or are carrying drugs (or maybe you've got all your possessions in a U-Haul), you really shouldn't have much trouble getting into the US, and doing it perfectly legally.  It's what you do once you're here that makes you an undocumented immigrant.</p>
<p>As far as I know, the US still recognizes passports from other countries, including Mexico.  Periodically we restrict people from certain countries, like Iran or Cuba, from entering the US.  To my knowledge we have never done that with Mexico.  It's not surprising that people from a very poor country look at a very rich country right next door, and say "why not go there?". </p>
