t showAvatars commentbody child " id="c77009110"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77009110,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;indialecarre&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;India LeCarre&quot;}"></div><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="http://indialecarre.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://m.static.newsvine.com/servista/imagesizer?file=indialecarre2F26BA61-70D9-8959-DEA9-9191F1C85113.jpg&width=60" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="false" /></a><a href="http://indialecarre.newsvine.com/">India LeCarre</a></div></div><div id="commentText_77009110" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>Clayartist:</p>
<p>Me either. Read the book by Tommy Frank called, WHAT'S THE MATTER WITH KANSAS?  It's an eye opener in this regard. He goes into how the GOP base does this, gets people to vote against their own interests.</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77009110,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3750262&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;19058290&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;indialecarre&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"></ul></div><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c77009110" title="Link to this comment">#8.3</a> - Thu Jun 20, 2013 3:53 PM EDT</span></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody child " id="c77014085"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77014085,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;fb-jimspeiser&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;James J. Speiser&quot;}"></div><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="http://fb-jimspeiser.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://m.static.newsvine.com/servista/imagesizer?file=null64D16F8E-8CBF-C33B-201E-06C3590F055A.jpg&width=60" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="false" /></a><a href="http://fb-jimspeiser.newsvine.com/">James J. Speiser</a></div></div><div id="commentText_77014085" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>May I also recommend "Deer Hunting with Jesus."  It's a glimpse into the mindset of the typical rural conservative voter.  They're not stupid...just frustrated with their lives, and what they perceive as the powers-that-be amassed against them.  Right-wing talk radio has given voice to their frustrations and inspired them to wield the one weapon they feel they have to fight back, and that's the power of the vote.  They can be easily duped into voting against their best interests, because, bless their hearts, they lack the education required to see the Big Picture and to know just what their best interests are. </p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77014085,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3750262&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;19058290&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;fb-jimspeiser&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"></ul></div><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c77014085" title="Link to this comment">#8.4</a> - Thu Jun 20, 2013 6:56 PM EDT</span></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody child " id="c77019536"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77019536,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;willstark2&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;WillStark&quot;}"></div><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="http://willstark2.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/av/60x60/msnbc.jpg" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="true" /></a><a href="http://willstark2.newsvine.com/">WillStark</a></div></div><div id="commentText_77019536" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>India,</p>
<p>I believe the gentleman's name is THOMAS Frank.  While you may be a close personal friend of the author, for many people "Tommy Frank" is the name of the general in charge during the Iraq War.</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77019536,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3750262&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;19058290&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;willstark2&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"></ul></div><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c77019536" title="Link to this comment">#8.5</a> - Fri Jun 21, 2013 1:26 AM EDT</span></div></div></div><div class="clearfix"><img class="replybutton" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_reply_mini.gif" width="35" height="12" alt="Reply" /></div><div class="commentcontainer"><span></span></div></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody " id="c77002225"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77002225,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;jo6pack&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;Jo6Pack&quot;}"></div><a name="star12"></a><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="#star13" class="noborder star"><img src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_star.gif" width="16" height="16" alt="" title="Jump To Next Highly Rated Comment" /></a><a href="http://jo6pack.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://m.static.newsvine.com/servista/imagesizer?file=jo6pack449A4D98-83AB-7435-5ACB-C2892EBADB1B.jpg&width=60" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="false" /></a><a href="http://jo6pack.newsvine.com/">Jo6Pack</a></div></div><div id="commentText_77002225" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><blockquote>
<p> I'm inclined to believe it has a lot to do with the way in which the literal electoral lines are drawn -- GOP lawmakers are confident that attitudes in  their red states and districts don't reflect national trends, so they couldn't care less what Americans in generally believe, so long as the folks who turn out for them on Election Day think the way they do.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>This is for sure the problem.  Pennsylvanians voted Democratic overwhelmingly, but we wound up with a Republican representation majority in Congress.  </p>
<p> I propose that Democrats should start registering RePUGnicant and vote in their primaries against the thugs; then go to the polls and vote the Democratic ticket.  Imagine how we could skew the polls.  Ha!</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77002225,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3750262&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;19058290&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;jo6pack&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">5 votes</div></li></ul></div><img class="replybutton" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_reply_mini.gif" width="35" height="12" alt="Reply" /><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c77002225" title="Link to this comment">#9</a> - Thu Jun 20, 2013 11:21 AM EDT</span><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody child " id="c77003657"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77003657,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;stevefitt1&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;steve fitt-3304217&quot;}"></div><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="http://stevefitt1.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/av/60x60/msnbc.jpg" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="true" /></a><a href="http://stevefitt1.newsvine.com/">steve fitt-3304217</a></div></div><div id="commentText_77003657" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>People, the modern computer has made it much much easier to accurately draw election district lines to get just the percentages of Repub and Dem voters that you want.</p>
<p>This is one reason why it will be NECESSARY to pass a Constitutional Amendment to make Gerrymandering a crime. Another is -- all the vote should have equal weight. Any scheme to make some votes better than others is unAmerican.</p>
<p>Someday soon the youth vote and the minority vote will make "Progressives" the veto proof majority in both houses and in many states. This will be the time to Ammend the Constitution to freeze in the lessons we have (or should have) learned in the 200+ year history of this nation. A list --</p>
<p>Equal rights for women, no Gerrymandering, money is not speech, Corporations are not people, the 1st duty of all Companies is to the "good of the American people", it is not OK for "the Press" to tell lies to the American people and call it News, it is OK for the Fed. Gov. to a) do Soc. Sec., b) do Medicare, c) do Healthcare for all, d) have a progressive tax system, e) tax net wealth, f) do internal improvements (aka infrastructure), fund (at least Fed.) elections from/with public money, and others.</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77003657,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3750262&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;19058290&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;stevefitt1&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">4 votes</div></li></ul></div><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c77003657" title="Link to this comment">#9.1</a> - Thu Jun 20, 2013 12:17 PM EDT</span></div></div></div><div class="clearfix"><img class="replybutton" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_reply_mini.gif" width="35" height="12" alt="Reply" /></div><div class="commentcontainer"><span></span></div></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody " id="c77002384"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77002384,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;johnseekingenlightenment&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;John seeking enlightenment&quot;}"></div><a name="star13"></a><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="#star14" class="noborder star"><img src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_star.gif" width="16" height="16" alt="" title="Jump To Next Highly Rated Comment" /></a><a href="http://johnseekingenlightenment.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://m.static.newsvine.com/servista/imagesizer?file=johnseekingenlightenment5261D6FA-7B26-00F1-2B9B-742E6557DE91.jpg&width=60" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="false" /></a><a href="http://johnseekingenlightenment.newsvine.com/">John seeking enlightenment</a></div></div><div id="commentText_77002384" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>The break between House members and popular opinion is a symptom of our elections being won or lost on the basis of fund raising instead of actually working to make ones district a better place.</p>
<p>Currently congressional elections are won by the candidate spending the most money over 90% of the time.  If we control for wackos (e.g. those advocating violence, such as Ms. Angle of Nevada, or having to deny being a witch such as Ms. O'Donnel of Delaware, or any male candidate that mentions rape) and only compare races with viable candidates, outspending ones opponent essentially guarantees victory.</p>
<p>As long as our system selects those pandering to the donor class the only polls that will matter will be fundraising pledges from the donor class. </p>
<p>Apparently the donor class wants cheap nannies, gardeners, to break unions, and to depress the wages of those who work for a living.  Do not be surprised when their minions in Congress vote accordingly.</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77002384,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3750262&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;19058290&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;johnseekingenlightenment&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">5 votes</div></li></ul></div><img class="replybutton" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_reply_mini.gif" width="35" height="12" alt="Reply" /><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c77002384" title="Link to this comment">#10</a> - Thu Jun 20, 2013 11:27 AM EDT</span><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody child " id="c77005050"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77005050,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;indialecarre&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;India LeCarre&quot;}"></div><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="http://indialecarre.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://m.static.newsvine.com/servista/imagesizer?file=indialecarre2F26BA61-70D9-8959-DEA9-9191F1C85113.jpg&width=60" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="false" /></a><a href="http://indialecarre.newsvine.com/">India LeCarre</a></div></div><div id="commentText_77005050" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>John, #10,</p>
<p>Can anything they do surprise us?  I doubt it.</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77005050,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3750262&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;19058290&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;indialecarre&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">1 vote</div></li></ul></div><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c77005050" title="Link to this comment">#10.1</a> - Thu Jun 20, 2013 1:14 PM EDT</span></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody child " id="c77019636"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77019636,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;willstark2&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;WillStark&quot;}"></div><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="http://willstark2.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/av/60x60/msnbc.jpg" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="true" /></a><a href="http://willstark2.newsvine.com/">WillStark</a></div></div><div id="commentText_77019636" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>During the 2012 campaign, the Democratic Party targetted Nevada (hardly a liberal bastion and then experiencing the highest unemployment in the nation) with volunteers, particularly from California.  <em>Months</em> prior to the state caucus, they did California-to-Nevada phonebanks and encouraged carpools of volunteers to register voters.  The RNC ignored the warnings of the state chair and thought they could overcome by "carpet bombing" the state with money and ad buys.  Instead, they didn't have enough volunteers to man all the caucus locations and the state chair resigned in frustration.</p>
<p>So: money doesn't always determine success (but it doesn't hurt !)</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77019636,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3750262&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;19058290&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;willstark2&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">1 vote</div></li></ul></div><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c77019636" title="Link to this comment">#10.2</a> - Fri Jun 21, 2013 1:43 AM EDT</span></div></div></div><div class="clearfix"><img class="replybutton" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_reply_mini.gif" width="35" height="12" alt="Reply" /></div><div class="commentcontainer"><span></span></div></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody " id="c77002524"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77002524,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;fb-steveeldridge100003111125657&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;Steve Eldridge&quot;}"></div><a name="star14"></a><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="#star15" class="noborder star"><img src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_star.gif" width="16" height="16" alt="" title="Jump To Next Highly Rated Comment" /></a><a href="http://fb-steveeldridge100003111125657.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://m.static.newsvine.com/servista/imagesizer?file=http3A2F2Fwww.newsvine.com2F_vine2Fimages2Fav2F120x1202F2F286174529.jpg&width=60" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="false" /></a><a href="http://fb-steveeldridge100003111125657.newsvine.com/">Steve Eldridge</a></div></div><div id="commentText_77002524" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>I've been posting the same response to all these issues. We need people to vote.</p>
<p>Republicans know they can get re-elected in their safe districts so why bother with issues that has National support?</p>
<p>Not that the Democrats are any better when it comes to safe election districts, but in the case of the Republicans they know they can easily walk into the next election without a single concern.</p>
<p>We are working on the assumption that money buys elections. It doesn't. Money buys momentum - or the appearance of it. Voter apathy is more powerful than voter turnout. No voters actually receive a check for turning out at the polls.</p>
<p>All too many voters just sit on the sidelines leaving the rest of us to watch in frustration as issue after issue goes unaddressed because voters fail to flex their power and show up at the polls. </p>
<p>It is a disgrace that we have only 30% to 50% show up at off-year elections.</p>
<p>If we increase the number of voters it will upset the order of incumbents winning races for no reason other than being already in office. It will also make House Members take the greater opinion of likely voters more seriously. </p>
<p>Clearly today they know that they do not have to do anything to win the next election.</p>
<p>We have reached the point where a "potted plant" can be elected to office if they are in the majority of the reliable voters in any given district. </p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77002524,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3750262&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;19058290&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;fb-steveeldridge100003111125657&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">8 votes</div></li></ul></div><img class="replybutton" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_reply_mini.gif" width="35" height="12" alt="Reply" /><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c77002524" title="Link to this comment">#11</a> - Thu Jun 20, 2013 11:32 AM EDT</span><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody child " id="c77004941"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77004941,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;gardenladytoo&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;GardenLadyToo&quot;}"></div><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="http://gardenladytoo.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/av/60x60/msnbc.jpg" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="true" /></a><a href="http://gardenladytoo.newsvine.com/">GardenLadyToo</a></div></div><div id="commentText_77004941" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>Money may not buy votes, but it does buy research.  As someone who works in cartography, not for political purposes but for city planning use, I have a goodly knowledge of this.  Gerrymandering districts has become so easy to do, street by street and block by block, that it's practical to gerrymander even state assembly districts--hence the takeover of statehouses by far, far right tea partiers.</p>
<p>The hardware and software is cheap and easily available.  The cost lies in the purchase of the data to crank through the programs.  Money does buy THAT, and has been buying it in spades.</p>
<p>I'm not a big fan of constitutional amendments, but I'm about ready for one that requires Federal legislative districts to be drawn exclusively on the basis of population, geographical compactness, and natural geographical boundaries, and specifically banning the use of any demographic, socioeconomic or voting data or any similar data.</p>
<p>Alas, both parties will oppose this.</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77004941,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3750262&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;19058290&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;gardenladytoo&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">3 votes</div></li></ul></div><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c77004941" title="Link to this comment">#11.1</a> - Thu Jun 20, 2013 1:10 PM EDT</span></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody child " id="c77005099"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77005099,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;indialecarre&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;India LeCarre&quot;}"></div><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="http://indialecarre.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://m.static.newsvine.com/servista/imagesizer?file=indialecarre2F26BA61-70D9-8959-DEA9-9191F1C85113.jpg&width=60" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="false" /></a><a href="http://indialecarre.newsvine.com/">India LeCarre</a></div></div><div id="commentText_77005099" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p><em>Alas, both parties will oppose this...</em></p>
<p>You can take that straight to the bank.</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77005099,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3750262&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;19058290&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;indialecarre&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">2 votes</div></li></ul></div><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c77005099" title="Link to this comment">#11.2</a> - Thu Jun 20, 2013 1:16 PM EDT</span></div></div></div><div class="clearfix"><img class="replybutton" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_reply_mini.gif" width="35" height="12" alt="Reply" /></div><div class="commentcontainer"><span></span></div></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody " id="c77002587"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77002587,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;lowtechcyclist&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;low-tech cyclist&quot;}"></div><a name="star15"></a><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="#star16" class="noborder star"><img src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_star.gif" width="16" height="16" alt="" title="Jump To Next Highly Rated Comment" /></a><a href="http://lowtechcyclist.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/av/60x60/msnbc.jpg" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="true" /></a><a href="http://lowtechcyclist.newsvine.com/">low-tech cyclist</a></div></div><div id="commentText_77002587" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>I think the media's both-sides-do-it-ism goes a long way to protect the GOP from the consequences of their radicalism. </p>
<p>If voters don't realize the GOP is much more radical to the right than the Dems are to the left - let alone aware that the Dems have effectively become a party of the center, with practically <em>nobody</em> out on the left - they're not likely to factor it into their voting.</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77002587,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3750262&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;19058290&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;lowtechcyclist&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">9 votes</div></li></ul></div><img class="replybutton" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_reply_mini.gif" width="35" height="12" alt="Reply" /><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c77002587" title="Link to this comment">#12</a> - Thu Jun 20, 2013 11:35 AM EDT</span><div class="clearfix"></div><div class="commentcontainer"><span></span></div></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody " id="c77002791"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77002791,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;joca41&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;joca41&quot;}"></div><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="http://joca41.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/av/60x60/msnbc.jpg" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="true" /></a><a href="http://joca41.newsvine.com/">joca41</a></div></div><div id="commentText_77002791" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>The truth is that immigration is not enough of a motivating factor to get people in favor off their butts and out to the polls. It is highly motivational for people who are vehemently against it like tea party members. This will more than likely show in the midterms which almost always has a low turnout. There are those in favor of immigration who will say oh well I dont need to vote if it happens it happens if it doesnt it doesnt. I would hope voter apathy changes in 2014 midterms but I'm very skeptical, I've seen it happen to many times.</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77002791,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3750262&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;19058290&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;joca41&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">3 votes</div></li></ul></div><img class="replybutton" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_reply_mini.gif" width="35" height="12" alt="Reply" /><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c77002791" title="Link to this comment">#13</a> - Thu Jun 20, 2013 11:44 AM EDT</span><div class="clearfix"></div><div class="commentcontainer"><span></span></div></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody " id="c77003171"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77003171,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;ponb&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;PonB&quot;}"></div><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="http://ponb.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/av/60x60/msnbc.jpg" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="true" /></a><a href="http://ponb.newsvine.com/">PonB</a></div></div><div id="commentText_77003171" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>Two words, Steve: "Watch 'Bulworth'"</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77003171,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3750262&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;19058290&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;ponb&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"></ul></div><img class="replybutton" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_reply_mini.gif" width="35" height="12" alt="Reply" /><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c77003171" title="Link to this comment">#14</a> - Thu Jun 20, 2013 12:00 PM EDT</span><div class="clearfix"></div><div class="commentcontainer"><span></span></div></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody " id="c77003205"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77003205,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;glenrunciter&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;Glen Runciter&quot;}"></div><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="http://glenrunciter.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/av/60x60/msnbc.jpg" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="true" /></a><a href="http://glenrunciter.newsvine.com/">Glen Runciter</a></div></div><div id="commentText_77003205" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>There is so much negotiation and compromising currently going on with this issue, and all of it seems to be in order to placate conservatives.</p>
<p>I wonder when it is that so much has been compromised away, that Democrats begin to walk away from it, because to vote for such a watered down version may assuage Republicans only to anger Hispanics.</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77003205,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3750262&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;19058290&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;glenrunciter&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">1 vote</div></li></ul></div><img class="replybutton" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_reply_mini.gif" width="35" height="12" alt="Reply" /><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c77003205" title="Link to this comment">#15</a> - Thu Jun 20, 2013 12:01 PM EDT</span><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody child " id="c77003407"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77003407,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;lebowskydude&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;Lebowsky Dude&quot;}"></div><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="http://lebowskydude.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/av/60x60/msnbc.jpg" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="true" /></a><a href="http://lebowskydude.newsvine.com/">Lebowsky Dude</a></div></div><div id="commentText_77003407" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>Adding border security without cow dung "triggers" is not going to alienate Hispanics. Yes, you are correct that enough is enough with larding this down, but this is a no-brainer that will allow hopefully enough Republicans to get it passed.</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77003407,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3750262&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;19058290&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;lebowskydude&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"></ul></div><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c77003407" title="Link to this comment">#15.1</a> - Thu Jun 20, 2013 12:08 PM EDT</span></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody child " id="c77003774"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77003774,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;glenrunciter&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;Glen Runciter&quot;}"></div><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="http://glenrunciter.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/av/60x60/msnbc.jpg" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="true" /></a><a href="http://glenrunciter.newsvine.com/">Glen Runciter</a></div></div><div id="commentText_77003774" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>I don't think the compromising is done yet...the House has yet to weigh in...if they ever do so.</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77003774,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3750262&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;19058290&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;glenrunciter&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"></ul></div><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c77003774" title="Link to this comment">#15.2</a> - Thu Jun 20, 2013 12:22 PM EDT</span></div></div></div><div class="clearfix"><img class="replybutton" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_reply_mini.gif" width="35" height="12" alt="Reply" /></div><div class="commentcontainer"><span></span></div></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody " id="c77003245"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77003245,&quot;authorDomain&quo