</p>
<p><a href="http://www.nbcnews.com/id/19747577/ns/world_news-the_new_york_times/"><a href="http://www.nbcnews.com/id/19747577/ns/world_news-the_new_york_times/">http://www.nbcnews.com/id/19747577/ns/world_news-the_new_york_times/</a></a></p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77003299,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3750262&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;19058290&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;cfimeiatpap&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"></ul></div><img class="replybutton" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_reply_mini.gif" width="35" height="12" alt="Reply" /><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c77003299" title="Link to this comment">#17</a> - Thu Jun 20, 2013 12:04 PM EDT</span><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody child " id="c77019665"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77019665,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;willstark2&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;WillStark&quot;}"></div><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="http://willstark2.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/av/60x60/msnbc.jpg" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="true" /></a><a href="http://willstark2.newsvine.com/">WillStark</a></div></div><div id="commentText_77019665" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>And what does "the Italian Oskar Schindler" have to do with anything ?  I hardly think any of these folks are going to be honored by Pope Francis or Yad Vashem.</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77019665,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3750262&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;19058290&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;willstark2&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"></ul></div><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c77019665" title="Link to this comment">#17.1</a> - Fri Jun 21, 2013 1:49 AM EDT</span></div></div></div><div class="clearfix"><img class="replybutton" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_reply_mini.gif" width="35" height="12" alt="Reply" /></div><div class="commentcontainer"><span></span></div></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody " id="c77003694"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77003694,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;dodgecitydem&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;Dodge City Dem&quot;}"></div><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="http://dodgecitydem.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://m.static.newsvine.com/servista/imagesizer?file=dodgecitydem043E3EB7-368E-DB8D-8432-F40BC83C100C.jpg&width=60" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="false" /></a><a href="http://dodgecitydem.newsvine.com/">Dodge City Dem</a></div></div><div id="commentText_77003694" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>Republicans are increasingly desperate to portray an image of concern, however insincere, for the plight of illegal immigrants. While their attempts are laughable at best, I think this is an excellent opportunity for Democrats to use some of the same obstructionist tactics employed by Republicans. By keeping any immigration reform D.O.A., and using the media to place the blame squarely on the sloped shoulders of the party of We Hate the Black President, Democrats can then come to the rescue and pass legislation in a mid-term elected, Democratic controlled, House and Senate before the 2016 election cycle. Sometimes it's fun to beat them at their own game.</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77003694,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3750262&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;19058290&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;dodgecitydem&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"></ul></div><img class="replybutton" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_reply_mini.gif" width="35" height="12" alt="Reply" /><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c77003694" title="Link to this comment">#18</a> - Thu Jun 20, 2013 12:18 PM EDT</span><div class="clearfix"></div><div class="commentcontainer"><span></span></div></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody " id="c77003930"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77003930,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;marko561&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;Marko56&quot;}"></div><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="http://marko561.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/av/60x60/msnbc.jpg" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="true" /></a><a href="http://marko561.newsvine.com/">Marko56</a></div></div><div id="commentText_77003930" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>The GOP sees <em>everything </em>through the lens of political gain. Will it hurt them or help them?</p>
<ol>
<li>Gun legislation: NRA said kill it so they did</li>
<li>Taxes on the wealthy: Wealthy donors said kill it so they did</li>
<li>Jobs Act: GOP doesn't want the economy to get better so they can blame Democrats during next election</li>
<li>Ending tax subsidies for oil companies: Oil companies said kill it so they did</li>
<li>Medicare: Wealthy donors are against it because they put more into the program than they take out. Privatizing Medicare would make it a juicy target</li>
<li>Immigration: helps to many potential future Democrats so the GOP is against it</li>
</ol>
<p>Note that in all of these examples, the GOP doesn't care how these issues help/hurt Americans in general. They care more about their own backsides than they do about us. "I got mine, F*CK YOU!"</p></p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77003930,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3750262&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;19058290&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;marko561&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">1 vote</div></li></ul></div><img class="replybutton" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_reply_mini.gif" width="35" height="12" alt="Reply" /><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c77003930" title="Link to this comment">#19</a> - Thu Jun 20, 2013 12:29 PM EDT</span><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody child " id="c77004189"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77004189,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;glenrunciter&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;Glen Runciter&quot;}"></div><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="http://glenrunciter.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/av/60x60/msnbc.jpg" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="true" /></a><a href="http://glenrunciter.newsvine.com/">Glen Runciter</a></div></div><div id="commentText_77004189" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>Too many tails wagging the dog...the Christian right, gun owners, right wing media, the Tea Party. And what do all of these groups have in common? None of them go gently into the good night. And that makes responding to them constantly an imperative.</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77004189,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3750262&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;19058290&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;glenrunciter&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"></ul></div><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c77004189" title="Link to this comment">#19.1</a> - Thu Jun 20, 2013 12:39 PM EDT</span></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody child " id="c77007358"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77007358,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;gardenladytoo&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;GardenLadyToo&quot;}"></div><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="http://gardenladytoo.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/av/60x60/msnbc.jpg" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="true" /></a><a href="http://gardenladytoo.newsvine.com/">GardenLadyToo</a></div></div><div id="commentText_77007358" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>And the Dems don't also see everything through their own political lens?</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77007358,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3750262&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;19058290&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;gardenladytoo&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"></ul></div><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c77007358" title="Link to this comment">#19.2</a> - Thu Jun 20, 2013 2:50 PM EDT</span></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody child " id="c77009899"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77009899,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;marko561&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;Marko56&quot;}"></div><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="http://marko561.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/av/60x60/msnbc.jpg" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="true" /></a><a href="http://marko561.newsvine.com/">Marko56</a></div></div><div id="commentText_77009899" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>Not <em>everything </em>like the GOP does.</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77009899,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3750262&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;19058290&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;marko561&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"></ul></div><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c77009899" title="Link to this comment">#19.3</a> - Thu Jun 20, 2013 4:17 PM EDT</span></div></div></div><div class="clearfix"><img class="replybutton" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_reply_mini.gif" width="35" height="12" alt="Reply" /></div><div class="commentcontainer"><span></span></div></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody " id="c77004593"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77004593,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;markfromshytown&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;Mark from Shytown&quot;}"></div><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="http://markfromshytown.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://m.static.newsvine.com/servista/imagesizer?file=MarkfromShytown4D004B99-B736-B51F-9680-512811C4F5FD.jpg&width=60" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="false" /></a><a href="http://markfromshytown.newsvine.com/">Mark from Shytown</a></div></div><div id="commentText_77004593" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>They don't answer to the polls...it's the $$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77004593,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3750262&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;19058290&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;markfromshytown&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"></ul></div><img class="replybutton" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_reply_mini.gif" width="35" height="12" alt="Reply" /><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c77004593" title="Link to this comment">#20</a> - Thu Jun 20, 2013 12:56 PM EDT</span><div class="clearfix"></div><div class="commentcontainer"><span></span></div></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody " id="c77004600"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77004600,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;fb-sandrabslemko&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;Sandra B. Slemko&quot;}"></div><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="http://fb-sandrabslemko.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://m.static.newsvine.com/servista/imagesizer?file=sandymaryland93324FD0-C383-7115-9856-32BC7873F056.jpg&width=60" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="false" /></a><a href="http://fb-sandrabslemko.newsvine.com/">Sandra B. Slemko</a><span class="facebookVia">via Facebook</span></div></div><div id="commentText_77004600" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>Here we go again, have aliens taken their common sense from their brain.  This is not rocket science.  Okay, if you do not want to be citizens, when are you going to deport them.  This affects their rich friends who use illegal aliens for their servents.  Now let us think about this.  As illegal aliens these people do not pay taxes, however use our medical services for free and government assistance, of which citizens have a hard time getting.  Now if we made them legal citizens, this would increase the government income and decrease the government assistance, unless the rich perfer to pay them under the table.   </p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77004600,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3750262&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;19058290&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;fb-sandrabslemko&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"></ul></div><img class="replybutton" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_reply_mini.gif" width="35" height="12" alt="Reply" /><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c77004600" title="Link to this comment">#21</a> - Thu Jun 20, 2013 12:56 PM EDT</span><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody child " id="c77011827"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77011827,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;rwsgate&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;rwsgate&quot;}"></div><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="http://rwsgate.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://m.static.newsvine.com/servista/imagesizer?file=rwsgate9AB52126-D0D7-F60C-01C2-FE66DB5C91C5.jpg&width=60" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="false" /></a><a href="http://rwsgate.newsvine.com/">rwsgate</a></div></div><div id="commentText_77011827" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>It would cost over $190 billion dollars to deport all 11 million undocumented immigrants, even if it were possible.  I agree that we should work towards a pathway to citizenship (for those that want US citizenship).  But I disagree with you on a couple of things.</p>
<p>First, most UI's pay taxes.  Employers deduct SS and Income taxes from their paychecks because it's the law.  This amounts to tens of billions of dollars every year that end up, unclaimed, in the US Treasury.  In addition, they pay the same sales and property taxes the rest of us pay.  They also buy food, products, services, all of which pay taxes and employ people.</p>
<p>Most UI's only go to the doctor when absolutely necessary, because it's hard to get and afford insurance.  Virtually every state in the union denies free services and governmental assistance to UI's.  You can't get on Medicaid if you are a UI.  No Social Security.  In most places you can't even get a driver's license.  Personally, I'd rather make them all get DL's, because it would make the roads a lot safer.</p>
<p>Right now UI's have no bargaining power.  Employers, particularly those who knowingly hire UI's, literally control their lives, as the UI's fear being turned in and deported.  Remove that barrier, and you remove the means to keep them as virtual slaves.  Then, just as you say, wages will rise and more taxes will be collected, which raises all boats.</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77011827,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3750262&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;19058290&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;rwsgate&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">2 votes</div></li></ul></div><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c77011827" title="Link to this comment">#21.1</a> - Thu Jun 20, 2013 5:20 PM EDT</span></div></div></div><div class="clearfix"><img class="replybutton" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_reply_mini.gif" width="35" height="12" alt="Reply" /></div><div class="commentcontainer"><span></span></div></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody " id="c77004640"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77004640,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;benetegiii&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;Benet&quot;}"></div><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="http://benetegiii.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://m.static.newsvine.com/servista/imagesizer?file=http3A2F2Fwww.newsvine.com2F_vine2Fimages2Fav2F120x1202Fbenetegiii-1434437152.jpg&width=60" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="false" /></a><a href="http://benetegiii.newsvine.com/">Benet</a></div></div><div id="commentText_77004640" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>I believe the thing that Steve Barnes is not considering is that in fact the Republicans are representing PEOPLE (as defined by Citizens United ruling).  The fact that voters number in 87% is irrelevant if 90% of corporate backers (other people) of the politician wish that he/she votes the other way.   </p>
<p>Making Corporations "people" has made individual American voters completely and utterly irrelevant.</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77004640,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3750262&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;19058290&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;benetegiii&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">3 votes</div></li></ul></div><img class="replybutton" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_reply_mini.gif" width="35" height="12" alt="Reply" /><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c77004640" title="Link to this comment">#22</a> - Thu Jun 20, 2013 12:58 PM EDT</span><div class="clearfix"></div><div class="commentcontainer"><span></span></div></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody " id="c77005297"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77005297,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;pcoleman31522&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;pcoleman31522&quot;}"></div><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="http://pcoleman31522.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/av/60x60/msnbc.jpg" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="true" /></a><a href="http://pcoleman31522.newsvine.com/">pcoleman31522</a></div></div><div id="commentText_77005297" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>A path to citizenship means that they can vote as citizens and they will not vote for republicans.</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77005297,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3750262&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;19058290&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;pcoleman31522&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">3 votes</div></li></ul></div><img class="replybutton" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_reply_mini.gif" width="35" height="12" alt="Reply" /><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c77005297" title="Link to this comment">#23</a> - Thu Jun 20, 2013 1:24 PM EDT</span><div class="clearfix"></div><div class="commentcontainer"><span></span></div></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody " id="c77006054"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77006054,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;richmjones&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;RichMJones@rcn.com&quot;}"></div><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="http://richmjones.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/av/60x60/msnbc.jpg" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="true" /></a><a href="http://richmjones.newsvine.com/">RichMJones@rcn.com</a></div></div><div id="commentText_77006054" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p><strong>What is the worst humanity can do? </strong>How would it be ranked, on a scale beginning with Cain and Abel and unending, unmentionable genocides? How would this scale be portrayed, viewable and understandable to a public that does not want to view it and does not want to understand it? Where in the world of ancient words is this plague mentioned?</p>
<p><strong>The blindness -</strong> 'public that does not want to view it and does not want to understand'.</p>
<p><strong>The -horrible-</strong> - 'portrayed, viewable and understandable to a public'.</p>
<p>If you believe in humanity, or if you believe in the gifts of GOD, or are consumed by infinite hate, then who would be your leader?</p>
<p><strong>&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; Sen. Ted Cruz (R-Texas) and the rest of Tea Party&hellip;</strong></p>
<p>Pick a topic and apply 'infinite hatred', and have the key to every republican, libertarian, conservative, right-wing, and this results in the unreasonable.</p>
<p><strong>Topic 'The American Dream' </strong>All born on this soil are granted citizen by the government. These citizens will be free to work independently, to settle disputes of property, and paternity with their neighbors. These citizens may by vote elect those who will best represent their community, and those representatives would provide ardent support for their elective community by assessing judging discussing with other representatives on issue affecting both. While in good representative hands the citizens are freer to busy their hands to attend to prosperity. It is the American Dream to come here to better yourself, your children, and the society you live and contribute to all the things that cannot be taken away from you.</p>
<p>The US grew from colonial rule of three million to one hundred times that, but today this has become clouded. The progress gained by the use energies denied human for millennia, has produced abundance, freedom and many changes, but these are all threatened by the same power that allowed them to happen. Freedom threatened by freedom, is a reversal that we are not prepared to fight against, it is the energy abundantly used that now has come to remove that freedom.</p>
<p>The first freedom loss is of movement, not movement itself, but of the enslavement caused by the necessity to move from place to place.</p>
<p>But the most freedom was lost, or given up, by the voter. The voter made too busy with the trinkets of prosperity, whose time is seldom spent to view the politics of decay. At one time the voter elected the best among them to represent all of them. It is an 'All for one and one for all' representative form of democracy that works. Whereas today the vote is largely wasted, voters vote for only those who have been selected by others, appointed by persons of wealth, funded by anonymous donors.  If we opt to vote for those who are placed before us, we cannot be selecting the best among us; there is no candidate that has been appointed by the owner of great wealth who has proven to be anything but the servant to that wealth.</p>
<p>The very foundation of the nation has been sold to the wealthy; where is the representative government design by citizens to elect by vote? Those who will best represent their community and those representatives would provide ardent support for their whole of the elective community by assessing, judging, discussing with other representatives on issue affecting both.</p>
<p><strong>The 'American Dream' but for who? </strong>The fantasy world does not exist, but it still useful to think about. Suppose a whole new set of people were to dream the American dream. It was widely advertised long before mass communications. Many were inspire from around the world, just on rumor, to move from home they'd known for centuries, to risk everything, leave all behind, and to go to new place where they would have to work harder than the every new how, and come to live the American Dream. If every born unchallenged American, had to leave all behind, forgo comfort, and possible work with blustered hands and move to strange place, few if any would take the challenge. Those same unchallenged American would connive, distort, disparage erect barriers, add conditions, and install fences and do all manner of things to themselves and to the world around them to stop the American Dream from spreading. The extremist is an unchallenged American, is exactly like, those left behind, in the old country who did not want to change, were discouraged by work but willing to live under unreasonable unelected governance is a system where exploiter alone rose to the heights of power.</p>
<p>There is more than one America, one of people who dream and work toward the American dream, and others who for reasons or infinite hatred believe that the American Dream magnificent but empty monument on some hill somewhere and that all we have to do is stay in the same place and do nothing enough and just move into that future with no work at all.</p>
<p>The Tea Party may purchase the news of the day all day, but they cannot ever be more than the hired help, to white wash the American Dream, never to seen again. Tea Party power is the power of infinite hate.</p>
<p>The outcome is clear and it certain, if all we do is focus on the unnecessary when we will have time to do the necessary, when shall we able work productively again?</p>
<p><strong>The immigration issue is 100% our fault, but we deny 100% of the responsibility and are determining to do 100% nothing.</strong></p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77006054,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3750262&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;19058290&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;richmjones&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"></ul></div><img class="replybutton" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_reply_mini.gif" width="35" height="12" alt="Reply" /><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c77006054" title="Link to this comment">#24</a> - Thu Jun 20, 2013 1:56 PM EDT</span><div class="clearfix"></div><div class="commentcontainer"><span></span></div></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody " id="c77006766"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77006766,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;theerik&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;theErik&quot;}"></div><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="http://theerik.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/av/60x60/msnbc.jpg" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="true" /></a><a href="http://theerik.newsvine.com/">theErik</a></div></div><div id="commentText_77006766" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p><em>GOP lawmakers are confident that attitudes in their red states and  districts don't reflect national trends, so they couldn't care less what  Americans in generally believe, so long as the folks who turn out for  them on Election Day think the way they do.</em></p>
<p>It's even more limited than that.  They are confident that their red districts will vote them in... but they really fear the activist base that is the other 15%.  If they don't keep them happy, they lose in the primary and never get to the point where the 90% actually matter.</p>
<p>The only way to stop this is to break the confidence that the red districts will continue to vote for the Republican label regardless of who the candidate is, and the only way to do that is to reach out and force the conversation in every district across the country.  And that is a very hard reach in this day of echo chambers and personalized news, where the voter never has to hear the other side if they don't want to.</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77006766,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3750262&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;19058290&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;theerik&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">1 vote</div></li></ul></div><img class="replybutton" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_reply_mini.gif" width="35" height="12" alt="Reply" /><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c77006766" title="Link to this comment">#25</a> - Thu Jun 20, 2013 2:27 PM EDT</span><div class="clearfix"></div><div class="commentcontainer"><span></span></div></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-paginate_Paginate"><a name="discussion_nav"></a><span class="jump">Jump to discussion page: </span><span class="curPageLink">1</span> <a href="http://maddowblog.msnbc.com/_news/2013/06/20/19058290-congress-vs-public-opinion?pc=25&sp=25#discussion_nav">2</a><div class="clearfix"><span></span></div></div></div><div class="commentcontainer"><div class="vine-p p-comment_CommentForm commentfields use_zinger"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;canLink&quot;:true,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3750262&quot;,&quot;isPrivate&quot;:false}"></div><a name="entercomment"></a><div class="commentbody"><div class="c_author"><div class="user"><a><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/av/60x60/msnbc.jpg" width="35" height="35" alt="Author ava